main event: Two boomerang-shaped objects were observed on radar and visually in Crestview, Florida on March 15, 1963.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be gray in color and smaller than a small plane.
The objects were observed to stop and hover at an altitude of 100 feet for about 2-3 seconds before disappearing.
The objects were observed to be in straight flight from east to west before stopping and hovering.
The report notes the extremely short duration of the sighting, which was likely due to the objects being birds.
The objects were observed by an Airman 3rd Class stationed at Eglin Air Force Base, who was considered a reliable source.
witnesses: Airman 3rd Class stationed at Eglin Air Force Base
